*[[Xylophone]] concerto: [[Toshiro Mayuzumi|Mayuzumi]]
*[[Yamaha GX-1]]: [[Yasushi Akutagawa|Akutagawa]]

Among the works of the prolific composer [[Alan Hovhaness]] may be noted ''Prayer of St. Gregory'' for trumpet and strings, though it is not a concerto in the usual sense of the term.

In the later 20th century the concerto tradition was continued by composers such as [[Peter Maxwell Davies|Maxwell Davies]], whose series of [[Strathclyde Concertos]] exploit some of the instruments less familiar as soloists.

